The newly appointed head coach of Warri Wolves has dumped the club on  mutual consent before the commencement of the new season after both parties could not arrive on a deal.
It could be recalled that Ngozi Elechi had joined the team  three weeks ago before the controversy.
According to our source both parties couldn’t reach an agreement which led to the exit of the former Plateau United midfielder who is now a coaches in the top flight Nigerian League.

			
